[2025-12-09 18:19:02,718][agent:client:fetch_single_interaction_prediction] [INFO] Fetch single interaction prediction {'timestamp': '1765304342', 'request_id': '53339d24-4dc0-45da-94aa-43e8bea2e38e', 'user': UserModel(gender=<Gender.MALE: 'male'>, user_name='user2026+roy.langern@zohomail.eu', country_code='DE', date_of_birth='2004-12-08', params=ParamsModel(topics=[TopicStanceModel(topic='politics', stance=<StanceType.INDIFFERENT: 'indifferent'>)])), 'video': VideoModel(video_id='7581810708921191702', url='https://www.tiktok.com/@europe_pulse/video/7581810708921191702', description='Last Hours for Europe’s Peace Proposal #eu #politics #geopolitics #security #safety #donaldtrump #news #ukrainewar #putin #unitedkingdom #germany #france  Volodymyr Zelenskyy met UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer, French President Emmanuel Macron and German Chancellor Friedrich Merz in London to finalize Europe’s peace framework for Ukraine.  Kyiv wants the proposal completed by Tuesday evening before it is handed to the United States, which is exploring ways to mediate an end to Russia’s war. Zelenskyy made clear that Ukraine will not accept any territorial concessions.  After London, Zelenskyy travelled to Brussels for follow-up talks with NATO Secretary General Mark Rutte, European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen and European Council President Antonio Costa. The goal: keep NATO, the EU, and Ukraine aligned on air defense, energy support and the political conditions for any future negotiations. ------------------------------------------------------ *Subscribe to Europe Pulse* Stay updated with the latest news from Europe.', author='europe_pulse')}
